author: crogers
msg: Fix for http://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEEHIVE-1033 - NetUI APT does not create UTF-8 encoded output in the generated XML documents for other multibyte encoded source files.

This fix explicitly sets the charset name to "UTF-8" for the PrintWriter we get with a call to com.sun.mirror.apt.Filer.createTextFile(), to match the "UTF-8" encoding for the XML declaration attribute in out generated files..
